This week’s guest on the “I’ve Never Said This Before” podcast is the brilliant @thesarahdrew, best known for playing the fan-favorite role of Dr. April Kepner for 9 seasons on @greysabc.This role catapulted Sarah into becoming a household name and even a trending hashtag (#JAPRIL) week after week. Now she is bringing some holiday cheer, starring in and executive producing the series, Mistletoe Murders out now on @hallmarkplus. Today, Sarah opens up about what she’s most proud of from her long-running character on Grey’s Anatomy, the ways she transformed as a person throughout her time playing April, how she worked through the pain of being let go from the series, the important lessons she learned through that difficult time, her thoughts on returning to Grey’s Anatomy, why her heart is singing with her latest project, Mistletoe Murders, if working on a Christmas project is as magical as it seems, why she feels that she is in the greatest chapter of her career, the sobering lesson she learned about the importance of being present, how a Pixar movie allowed her to really acknowledge the good and bad of her emotions, if she agrees that Mariah is the queen of Christmas, and so much more. “I’ve Never Said This Before” is available to listen to for free on Apple Podcasts, Spotify, iHeart & wherever you listen. Subscribe and download this episode now! 

#IveNeverSaidThisBefore #SarahDrew #GreysAnatomy #Greys #MistletoeMurders #Hallmark

This week’s guests on the “I’ve Never Said This Before” podcast is the lovely @msbethanyjoylenz who became a household name by playing the beloved role of Haley James Scott in One Tree Hill. Her new memoir, “Dinner for Vampires,” is out now and chronicles her spending a decade in a cult, and her quest to break free. Today, Joy opens up about how she went from going to a weekly bible study to being fully immersed in a cult, the red flags about this group that she now realizes she ignored, the first moment she really began feeling being isolated from her friend and family, joining Once Tree Hill and juggling her work life with the cult, what makes her smile when she thinks back on her fan-favorite role on the series, that iconic kissing in the rain scene, the latest on a potential reboot, why thinking about the kindness from her cast after going through a difficult time makes her emotional, the moment she realized the cult took over $2 million from her, how she was able to most past feeling self-loathing to start forgiving herself, what she wants to say to her parents for the first time and so much more. “I’ve Never Said This Before” is available to listen to for free on Apple Podcasts, Spotify, iHeart & wherever you listen. Subscribe and download this episode now!

A new Louisiana law, effective August 1, makes it illegal to stand within 25 feet of a police officer engaged in law enforcement duties after being ordered to stay back. ⁠
⁠
Supporters, including Gov. Jeff Landry and bill author Rep. Bryan Fontenot, argue it enhances officer safety. ⁠
⁠
While critics, including former Gov. John Bel Edwards and the ACLU of Louisiana, contend it infringes on citizens’ First Amendment rights to observe and hold police accountable. ⁠
⁠
Violating the law can result in a fine of up to $500, 60 days in jail, or both.

Westleaf Human Rights: The ongoing genocide in the DRC represents one of the gravest humanitarian crises of our time. It is marked by unspeakable acts of violence, systemic human rights abuses, and the displacement of millions. This atrocity is not just a regional disaster; it is a global moral failing that demands urgent and decisive action from the international community. We must collectively condemn these acts of brutality and work tirelessly to support peace, justice, and the restoration of dignity for the Congolese people. Silence and inaction are not options; they only serve to perpetuate the suffering and bloodshed. It is our shared responsibility to advocate for the end of this genocide, ensure accountability for the perpetrators, and provide substantial aid to the victims. The world must unite in demanding an immediate cessation of violence and a comprehensive commitment to rebuilding and healing in DRC.

Tomorrow, November 8th, we’ll be releasing the most important documentary ever made about the Marines who fought in Fallujah, Iraq 20 years ago this month.

Featuring original interviews with 25 Marines who fought and bled on those streets alongside never before seen footage of the combat they endured, this is a piece of American history you cannot miss.

Marines, we’re proud to tell your stories and ensure your valiant efforts are recorded for generations to come. We’ll never stop serving those who serve.

“War Pigs: Block to Block in Fallujah” premieres tomorrow on the Black Rifle Coffee YouTube channel.

We gathered over 50 Marines at @blackriflecoffee headquarters to sing the Marine Corps hymn and cut an epic cake for the 249th birthday of the greatest fighting force the world has ever known!

These Marines span generations, with veterans who fought everywhere from Iwo Jima to Fallujah, Sangin, and Helmand, and everywhere in between. 

This is what it’s all about, bringing people together over a cup of coffee, bonding over service in the process. Happy birthday, Marines!

Stay caffeinated! 🇺🇸☕️

20 years ago this month, Marines pushed into Fallujah, kicking off one of the bloodiest battles of the War on Terror.

@jackmandaville and @ryfitting, both Marine Corps veterans themselves, interviewed 25 of these Marines over the past few months—many of them speaking about their experiences for the first time. Then they gathered video and photo documentation of the battle—much of it never released publicly before.

The result of their efforts? They recorded not just Marine Corps history, but American history.

“Warpigs: House to House in Fallujah” is live now on @blackriflecoffee YouTube channel.

This is the most important documentary you can watch this Veterans Day weekend. Semper Fi, Marines! Thank you for your bravery and incredible sacrifice. We will never forget.

The 2024 #Ford Raptor R picks up the same visual adjustments that other F-150s get this year, which includes a revised front end featuring headlights that better integrate with the grille. Thanks to a new hood offering additional airflow, Ford was able to boost the supercharged 5.2-liter V-8 to 720 horsepower, a gain of 20. The Fox Dual Live Valve dampers also now allow control over both rebound and compression, instead of the previous setup's compression alone. #Honda unveiled the first-ever V-3 engine to feature forced induction. The engine is designed for large-displacement motorcycles and features two pistons on one side and one on the other. The engine is water-cooled with the pistons arranged in a 75-degree Vee—two of which tilt forward with the third tilting rearward. Tap the link in our bio for more info.
.

Both the #Ford F-150 Tremor and #Ram 1500 Rebel sit as off-road alternatives to their more extreme counterparts; the Raptor and the RHO respectively. Ford's Tremor is powered by a 400-hp 5.0-liter V-8, whereas the Rebel has a 420-hp twin-turbo 3.0-liter inline-six. Both the Tremor and the Rebel roll on 33-inch all-terrain tires, and they have underbody skid plates and tow hooks to help them survive the toughest conditions. The 2025 #Ford Bronco lineup adds two special editions. The Stroppe Edition is inspired by the Stroppe Baja Broncos from the 1960s and '70s with a distinctive tri-tone livery that resembles the old-school version. In 1997, we tested the #Porsche 911 GT1's street-legal homologation. Built solely to allow its pure-racing analogue a shot at the 24 Hours of Le Mans, it feels like a purebred race car—because it pretty much is. The flat-six engine, which produces 536 horsepower, sits right behind the cockpit bulkhead, rather than hanging out behind the axle line, and the long tail slopes down over the rear­-mounted six-speed gearbox. The body is made of Kevlar and carbon-fiber with the doors being almost weightless, but they slam shut with the same solid, well-engineered feel of a "normal" 911. Tap the link in our bio for the full archived review.
.

The Wisconsin-based #Ringbrothers revealed their latest resto-mod beauty known as INVADR. Based off a 1987 #Buick Grand National, the build stays close to its roots by keeping a 3.8-liter V-6, but the INVADR’s powertrain features custom hand-ported aluminum heads, a Bryant Racing billet crank, and twin Precision GEN 2 62mm turbochargers. At 50 psi of boost it’s good for 2000 hp, but for streetability, it’s been dropped back to 32 psi. What car do you want the Ringbrothers to get their hands on next?

3 dirty secrets about plastic cosmetics packaging: 

1️⃣ 95% of your plastic cosmetic packaging ends up in the landfill and our oceans every year 

2️⃣ Cosmetics companies want you to think you can recycle plastic, but it’s basically a myth

3️⃣ Cosmetic companies use ‘green’ buzz words and programs to mislead you 

+++
4️⃣ steps you can take in the right direction: 

1. Educate yourself, be curious and ask questions. Do not fall for Greenwashing. 

2. Purchase skincare and cosmetics that use little-to-no plastic packaging. 

3. Buy in glass packaging because glass can be recycled over and over again without being compromised. 

4. Choose companies that offer real refill options. Beware of refillable containers because they’re often made from plastic, and the manufacturing and transportation of said refillable containers may be marketed as eco-friendly but digging deeper reveals that most are really no different than single-use products. As a reminder, less than 1% of single-use plastic packaging is recycled.

3 dirty secrets about plastic cosmetics packaging: 

1️⃣ 95% of your plastic cosmetic packaging ends up in the landfill and our oceans every year 

2️⃣ Cosmetics companies want you to think you can recycle plastic, but it’s basically a myth

3️⃣ Cosmetic companies use ‘green’ buzz words and programs to mislead you 

+++
4️⃣ steps you can take in the right direction: 

1. Educate yourself, be curious and ask questions. Do not fall for Greenwashing. 

2. Purchase skincare and cosmetics that use little-to-no plastic packaging. 

3. Buy in glass packaging because glass can be recycled over and over again without being compromised. 

4. Choose companies that offer real refill options. Beware of refillable containers because they’re often made from plastic, and the manufacturing and transportation of said refillable containers may be marketed as eco-friendly but digging deeper reveals that most are really no different than single-use products. As a reminder, less than 1% of single-use plastic packaging is recycled.

Understanding Hair Loss: Causes and Solutions for Men

Hair loss can be a frustrating experience, but knowing the causes and solutions can help you take control. Here’s what you need to know:

🔍 Causes of Hair Loss

Genetics: The most common cause, often known as male pattern baldness, is hereditary and can start as early as your 20s.
Hormonal Changes: Changes in testosterone levels can impact hair growth. Conditions like androgenetic alopecia are linked to hormone levels.
Stress: High levels of stress can lead to hair thinning and shedding.
Poor Diet: Lack of essential nutrients, like iron and vitamins, can affect hair health.
Medical Conditions: Diseases such as thyroid disorders and autoimmune conditions can contribute to hair loss.
Medications: Certain drugs, including those for high blood pressure and depression, may have hair loss as a side effect.

Vegan Power Caesar
Serves 5
Ready in 30 minutes
Ingredients:
Dressing
1 package silken tofu
2 tbsp olive oil
1/4 tsp salt
1 tsp Dijon mustard
1 large lemon squeezed
1 clove garlic
1 tsp capers
2 tbsp nutritional yeast
2 tbsp hemp seeds
Black pepper to your tastes
Crispy Lentils
15 oz can lentils drained
3 sprays olive oil
1 pinch salt
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp smoked paprika
Salad
1 bunch Dino Kale chopped small
½  bunch purple kale, stemmed and chopped in bite-sized pieces
Instructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400F. On a sheet pan add lentils, olive oil, salt, smoked paprika and Cajun spice. Mix well and bake for 20 minutes, turning once halfway. Let cool.
2. Make dressing by putting tofu, olive oil, salt, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, garlic, salt, black pepper, nutritional yeast and capers in a blender and blend until smooth. 
3. In a large bowl, add the kale and a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt, then massage with your hands to soften the leaves. Add the crispy lentils and the dressing and toss well.
4. Enjoy within 2-3 days for best quality or dress to order and enjoy for 4.

For many years, the hulking Riverview condo building has been a sought-after place to live in Cambridge, its 66 units of high-end housing offering residents an enviable perch overlooking the Charles River. Many residents in the Mount Auburn Street structure are seniors — some who moved there in retirement and others who have spent decades there. Most own, some rent.⁠
⁠
Now, in what one resident called a “nightmare” scenario, they will all need to leave, quickly, for at least a year, officials say.⁠
⁠
Newly discovered structural issues in the reinforced concrete building, which was built in the early 1960s, have led to concerns about its long-term safety, according to the property management company that oversees it. Residents have agreed to move out of the building beginning Monday and over the next four weeks to make way for necessary interior remediation work.⁠
⁠
Click on the link in our bio to read the full story.⁠
⁠
✍️: Spencer Buell⁠
📸: David L. Ryan/Globe Staff

Apartment hunters in New York City got good news on Wednesday when the City Council there passed a bill that would largely compel landlords, not tenants, to cover broker fees, those expensive charges tacked on to the cost of signing an apartment lease.⁠
⁠
Will Boston, one of the few other cities where such fees are commonplace, follow suit? Sorry, renters: Don’t count on it.⁠
⁠
Over the years, city and state lawmakers have periodically pushed to modify broker fees. But such efforts have gotten little more than lip service on Beacon Hill.⁠
⁠
Click on the link in our bio to read more about the situation in Boston and what effects such a change might have.⁠
⁠
✍️: Dana Gerber and Andrew Brinker⁠
📸: Erin Clark/Globe Staff

Carrying on a cherished tradition, a couple from Nova Scotia has donated Boston’s official Christmas tree.⁠
⁠
This year’s tree is a 45-foot white spruce from the Mattie Settlement in Antigonish County, the city’s parks and recreation department said. It was donated by Hugh and Liz Ryan, who said they’ve “watched this tree grow from a young sapling to its present height for the last 30 years.”⁠
⁠
The Canadian province has sent Boston a tree every year since 1971 in gratitude for the help the city provided after the Halifax Explosion in 1917, according to Nova Scotia’s government website. This year, the tree will begin its journey next week, ahead of the December tree lighting on Boston Common.⁠
⁠
Click on the link in our bio to read the full story.⁠
⁠
✍️: Sabrina Lam⁠
📸: Courtesy of Communications Nova Scotia

In the wake of last month’s announcement that she would close and sell her remaining restaurants, chef Barbara Lynch is now being sued by the City of Boston for nearly $1.7 million in unpaid personal property taxes.⁠
⁠
According to a lawsuit filed Wednesday in Suffolk Superior Court, the celebrated-but-embattled chef has tallied up a “vast unpaid amount of taxes” across her seven restaurants in Fort Point, the South End, and Beacon Hill that have gone unaddressed for over a decade.⁠
⁠
Lynch, a daughter of South Boston whose trajectory from public housing to the upper echelons of fine dining put her among an elite class of celebrity chefs, has over the past several years, faced a series of debilitating hardships that have upended her career and her hometown restaurant empire. Click on the link in our bio to read the full story.⁠

Loring Tu has taught mathematics at Tufts University for 38 years, while quietly building a fortune worth millions from some well-placed stock investments. Now, the math professor is looking at retiring from Tufts a year from now, and he’s planning on giving much of his money to the Medford university.⁠
⁠
Tufts on Wednesday announced that Tu has donated an “eight-figure gift” — more than $10 million, but the school won’t say how much more — to the $2 billion-plus Tufts endowment, in honor of his grandfather, Tsungming Tu, who died in 1986. In return, Tufts is naming its Science and Engineering Complex after the elder Tu, considered the father of Taiwanese modern medicine.⁠
⁠
“Tufts needs a bigger endowment in order to offer more financial aid for its students,” said Tu. “I’ve had a happy time here for 38 years. ... I’d like to give something back.”⁠
⁠
Click on the link in our bio to read the full story.⁠
⁠

In May 2019, Jenée Walker started a list of attributes she wanted in her next romantic partner on her phone’s Notes app: loving, consistent, considerate.

She continued to tweak the list into the summer of 2020, removing items she eventually deemed “superficial,” paring her requirements down to a few firm green flags. Then, she turned the list on herself.

“I started working on the things I felt like I could do better if I wanted them from someone else,’” Walker, now 34, says.

While exploring Hinge four years ago, she swiped yes on Kerry Casting. They had previously met in 2014 while working for Hertz. In the following years, they ran into each other at nightclubs in Boston and even matched on dating apps, exchanging quick hellos, but never more.

But everything changed when they matched again in August 2020.

Click the link in our bio to read more about their love story.

Sorry, Massachusetts. $5 beers aren’t in your immediate future.⁠
⁠
State lawmakers appear set once again to reject an effort to allow discounted drink promotions in Massachusetts, after they left a proposed “happy hour” measure out of a $4 billion economic development package set for a final vote soon. (While happy hour specials are common in many parts of the country, Massachusetts in 1984 outlawed them amid heightened concerns about drunk driving.)⁠
⁠
The amendment could have allowed specials on beer, wine, and cocktails before 10 p.m., so long as beverage prices do not change during the discounted period, and any promotions are advertised at least three days in advance. It would not have automatically permitted happy hour statewide, but rather left it up to cities and towns to opt in and design their own rules.⁠

The Onion’s most cutting joke of all time might have come on Thursday, when the satirical news site announced it plans to acquire Infowars, the website run by conspiracy theorist Alex Jones that has spread disinformation. The planned purchase has a very serious side to it: The deal was backed by families of victims in the mass shooting at Sandy Hook Elementary School in Newtown, Conn., which Jones repeatedly claimed was a hoax, costing him $1.5 billion in legal damages.⁠
⁠
But behind the deal is the relatively new leader of the Onion, Ben Collins, a former star NBC News reporter and a Massachusetts native, who grew up in Salem and later Byfield. He’s also a self-described “Masshole” who said he saw the opportunity to buy Infowars out of bankruptcy as the kind of in-your-face dare that he was born to take.⁠
⁠
“Ben wants to do what’s good and what’s funny,” said Mark Leccese, a former Emerson journalism professor who taught Collins. “The Onion buying Infowars is both good and ridiculously funny.”⁠

“The Knowledge Keepers,” Alan Michelson’s finished sculptures of Marden and of Nipmuc descendant Andre StrongBearHeart Gaines Jr., both real-life cultural leaders in their Massachusetts communities, were installed Thursday morning to flank the main entrance of the Museum of Fine Arts (@mfaboston).

For more than 100 years, the sole adornment at the museum’s Huntington Avenue front door has been “Appeal to the Great Spirit,” a sculpture of an Indigenous man on horseback in a feathered headdress, arms stretched wide in an apparent plea for mercy. Earlier this year, the MFA announced an annual commission for an artist to make new work for its facade. Michelson, 71, who is a Mohawk member of the Six Nations of the Grand River, has both the distinction, and the burden, of going first.

“No one would ever take them for Native American stereotype,” Michelson said.

Read more at the link in the @bostonglobelife bio.

✍️: Murray Whyte (@murrayscottwhyte)
📸: Photo by Steven G. Smith

Dozens of pharmacies have closed in Boston this past decade, raising red flags across the city about access to life-saving medications. Now Boston officials hope to bridge the gaps with a temporary program that provides free Lyft rides for seniors in hard-hit parts of the city to drug stores and other health services.⁠
⁠
The program — a collaboration between the City of Boston and the Urban League of Massachusetts called the Holistic Health Access Initiative — will offer no-charge rides to “wellness services" to residents over 60 in Roxbury, Dorchester, and Mattapan. A spokesperson for the Urban League said they expect to provide free rides through the winter. Participants are limited to five rides a month.⁠

Meet Etsy seller Sarah Miller!
When Sarah was 15, her mother taught her how to peyote circular bead. Born and raised in Big Pine, CA and an enrolled member of the Big Pine Paiute Tribe, she always looked at beading as a beautiful piece of being a Native American. When Sarah’s father passed away, she felt it was important to honor him by learning more about beading.

“I absolutely love National Native American Heritage Month because we get to see so many people celebrating who we are, letting people see we are still around and we are beautiful proud people!”

Find more beaded jewelry and accessories in Sarah’s Etsy shop @inspired.natives

@theweeknd has debuted a ‘Hurry Up Tomorrow’ special edition vinyl LP featuring artwork by longtime collaborator @hajimesorayamaofficial.⁠
⁠
The upcoming variant’s cover sees the renowned Japanese artist slightly depart from his signature look in order to capture the record’s theme of rebirth. Sorayama designs an image of a child submerged under water, dressed in a experimental suit with different cords attached; the cover is still attached to the artist’s more traditional work of technology and sci-fi, but also expresses The Weeknd’s desire of resurrection.⁠
⁠
It will mark the final installment in The Weeknd’s latest album trilogy, which is also comprised of ‘After Hours’ and ‘Dawn FM.’ In addition to its release, the project will be expanded into a feature film starring Jenna Ortega, Barry Keoghan and The Weeknd himself.⁠
⁠
Stay tuned for an official release date for ‘Hurry Up Tomorrow.’⁠

It’s November which means it’s National Adoption Awareness and Permanacy Month 🤍

As an adoptee I’ve experienced first hand how much unconditional love, support and stability can change someone’s life. In my case, it perhaps saved my life, which taught me the importance of family and the power of gratitude from an early age. I had the most fulfilling and colourful childhood one could ask for. My parents created such a safe space that even though they told my little sister and I at a young age we were adopted, we never once thought that made us any different or made to feel less than. We’re a family bound by love, and that runs far deeper than blood.

Every child deserves a safe and nurturing home, but unfortunately not everyone is as lucky. There was only 334 adoptions in Australia in 2019-20. There’s currently 46,000 children in our foster care system, many who go from place to place with their belongings in a garbage bag. I can’t begin to tell you how much I mentally spiral when I start thinking about the staggering amount of children who are displaced and how this may have long term effects on their futures, especially infants born into adoption from day one, but that’s a story for another day. 

This is why I work with @adoptchangeau because their mission is so important; to help positively change the future for displaced children by providing support resources, training, education and programs to families and communities caring for them or to the children themselves.  This Yesvember is extra special because I’ve teamed up with @adoptchangeau to design this year’s hats and tote bag, where 100% of the proceeds go towards helping these children in need. You can buy them via the link in my bio. 

I’ll also be doing a Q&A on their Instagram tomorrow from 1-2pm AEST so if you have any questions about adoption or the ways you can help, please head over there and leave your question in the question box in their stories.

#Yesvember #AHomeForEveryChild

OUT NOW / VITALY FW24 “OPULENCE” / DROP 01

Vitaly’s FW24 collection, titled “OPULENCE,” was inspired by the extravagance of New York City’s infamous nightlife scene in the late 1970s. This collection of show-stopping accessories reimagines the glamor of Studio54 through a decidedly Vitaly lens, pairing lavish design cues with the energy of the punk movement — a subculture that was gaining momentum in NYC during this same time period. When designing this collection, we challenged ourselves to consider what it would look like if the punks infiltrated Studio54, bypassing the lines and celebrities, crashing high-society’s most notable party. What would happen if the ostentatious jewelry of the era was recontextualized through a punk lens? The result is our take on opulence — a collection that is just as rebellious as it is luxurious.

Q: Why is the skin barrier so important for acne? 

A: An acne cycle can never improve if the barrier is damaged. When the skin barrier becomes compromised, it slows the healing process. When the barrier is weakened, it cannot respond correctly to active acne ingredients. In fact, a compromised barrier will over-respond to dysfunction as it can no longer protect itself. So it becomes dry, tight, flaky, and red – creating an atmosphere where acne bacteria will thrive.

Inspired by the philosophy of corneotherapy, our Acne + Pore Activists focus on repairing, maintaining and safeguarding the skin barrier. 🤎

Можно ли при помощи йоги, усилить или придать рельеф телу?
А можно ли похудеть с помощью йоги?
Я часто слышу эти вопросы и часто слышу утверждение, что только зал, веса могу дать вам мышцы, силу, рельеф…
Я знаю многих практиков за и против. Каждого уважаю и ценю его позицию.
Скажу за себя. Все зависит от того, какой йогой вы занимаетесь.
Если добавлять в нее интервальность, добавлять вариации силовых - то определенно. Можно еще добавить утяжелители и словить вообще интересные ощущения. 
Сегодня как раз в сториз одного преподавателя видела ее коммент по поводу хорошего рельефа бедра и ягодицы, а она занимается только йогой.
Важен не сам метод, а возможность вариативности в нем вас и вашего тела, мышления.
А вы как считаете?

«Обязательно выполните упражнение на две стороны, потому что иначе будет одна попа, а второй не будет. А то после нашего выпуска пол России будут ходить с одной попой» - цитата из одного видео и диалога двух преподавателей йоги, к занятию с акцентом на мышцы бедра и ягодиц.
Забавный факт, имеет место быть в реальности преподавания.
В основном мы показываем положения/последовательности на одну сторону, а на вторую уже больше ходим по залу поправляя или помогая вам углубить положение.
Развивая тем самым свою профессиональную асимметрию тела и прокачивая только одну свою сторону тела или одну попу)
И как вчера мы посмеялись с моим другом и учителем йоги, что вот уже более 6 лет ее преподавания у нее активно впахивает только правая сторона.
Так что если при взгляде на преподавателя вам кажется, что одна сторона у него более рельефная или одна ягодица подтянутая, то вам не кажется😄

Low libido affects 1 in 5 men, over 1 in 4 premenopausal women, and over 1 in 2 menopausal women.

But how do you know if you’re just not in the mood or if there’s more at play?

Libido is complex. It’s ignited by an interplay of factors—biological, psychological, and even social.

Libido can shift for a variety of reasons, such as exhaustion, anxiety, certain medications, and pregnancy. But hidden health issues can also be the cause, including:
-Chronic stress
-Nutrient deficiencies
-Hormonal imbalances
-Thyroid issues
-Autoimmune conditions
-Diabetes
-Kidney disease

It’s not just being busy or getting older. Test the biomarkers that influence desire, get answers, and make changes.

What started as a breakfast food has become a symbol of Big Food’s profit-driven agenda. 

Kellogg’s cereals in the U.S. contain a host of chemicals and additives linked to chronic disease, behavioral issues, and metabolic dysfunction, while their Canadian counterparts are formulated with significantly cleaner ingredients… 

But this isn’t just about cereal—it’s about the broken system that allows harmful ingredients to flood our food supply, impacting everything from physical health to mental well-being.

Disease doesn’t happen overnight—it’s a slow progression from wellness to dysfunction, illness, and eventually more serious conditions. 

Subtle shifts in your body—things like low energy, poor digestion, or brain fog—are often the first clues. By identifying and addressing these early, you can prevent bigger issues down the road.

Your body is always giving you signals. The question is, are you paying attention?

Did you know that mouth breathing can change the shape of your face and impact your overall health? 🌬️

Breathing through your nose helps filter out harmful pathogens, improves oxygen intake, and supports healthy craniofacial development. 

Mouth breathing, on the other hand, can lead to recessed chins, droopy eyes, and even higher risks of sleep apnea and infections.

Luckily you can reverse these effects at any age! Start by practicing nasal breathing, incorporating tougher foods into your diet, and even taping your mouth at night to train proper breathing habits. Swipe for more info.

By tuning into your hunger cues and avoiding overeating, you can boost digestion, reduce inflammation, and even promote longevity. It’s been scientifically proven: this simple practice can lower your risk of chronic disease and help you feel more balanced overall.

butternut squash mac & cheese -
••• slice open two small butternut squash, remove the seeds, then cover in olive oil & salt
••• bake at 400F for 30 minutes
••• once the squash is done baking, let is cool, then transfer all of the insides to a blender
••• to the blender also add in 3/4 cup unsweetened milk, 3 TBSP nutritional yeast (or real cheese), 1/3 cup soaked cashews, 1/2 tsp garlic powder, 1/2 tsp onion powder, 1/2 tsp salt, some black pepper & blend
••• add in 1/4-1/3 cup pasta water if needed to thin
••• transfer to cooked pasta & mix until all the noodles are fully coated
••• transfer pasta to an oven safe dish, top w cheese (i’m using cheddar, but a combo of cheddar + smoked gouda is delish!) & bake at 350F for 20 minutes, then broil for 5
••• top w chopped chives & enjoy!! 🧡

Volevamo contribuire al cleanup delle nostre bellissime spiagge e abbiamo scoperto l'incredibile progetto "Barbie adotta una spiaggia" di @marevivoonlus , il R.Party.Amo del WWF (@wwfitalia ) e molte realtà con cui collaborare come @legambiente @project_mare @plasticfreeit @rifiuti_amo_ci .
In www.italia.it ( @italiait ) abbiamo anche letto: "Come diventare volontari per la pulizia delle spiagge”, grande articolo!

Purtroppo abbiamo anche capito che l'industria del riciclaggio può essere altamente inquinante. Da un lato ripulisci le spiagge e dall’altro… Un post di @matteo.ward che mostra migliaia di jeans abbandonati ci ha spaventate.
Allora abbiamo detto: “Pulire e riciclare non basta. Dobbiamo incentivare l'UpCycling”

"Che cos'è l'UpCycling Sofi?"

"È un metodo fantastico che piacerà a un'artista come te Eli, perché unisce arte e riciclaggio!"
"Wow! Spiegati!"
"Significa riusare in modo creativo i materiali di scarto, superflui e le eccedenze, specialmente nell'industria della moda.  Con questi materiali si creano nuovi prodotti con ingegno e creatività."
"Però sulle spiagge trovi di tutto."
"Certo, i rifiuti vanno trattati con i metodi del riciclaggio, ma tutto il resto: teli, asciugamani, capi di abbigliamento che trovi a bizzeffe… può essere impiegato per creare nuovi prodotti.”
"È un'idea fantastica, bisogna proporre attività di UpCycling a tutte le associazioni. Pensa a come si divertirebbero i bambini delle scuole."
“Ed è anche molto educativo!"

"Dai forza! Separiamo i rifiuti da riciclare dai materiali utili per l'UpCycling e vediamo che cosa salta fuori."

Ed ecco che cosa abbiamo creato con quello che abbiamo raccolto in spiaggia: vi piace? Proverete anche voi?
Speriamo che l’UpCycling si diffonda, non risolverà tutti i problemi, ma è un bel passo avanti.

"Eli, sai che molti giovani designer creano progetti di UpCycling?"

“Davvero? Chissà che risultati con lo stile e la creatività italiane!”

In primavera gli occhi si possono danneggiare per l’esposizione ai raggi Ultra Violetti (UV). E poi capitano giornate di vento pazzesco con terra, sabbia e polvere che ti colpisce negli occhi! Anche il polline può dare fastidio agli occhi.

Ecco i nostri consigli per te.

Indossa occhiali da sole che abbiano una protezione completa dai raggi UV. L’etichetta dovrebbe indicare: "100% di protezione UV" oppure "UV400".
Se lavori vicino a fonti d’acqua o liquidi o dove ci sono molte superfici metalliche scegli delle lenti polarizzate perché riducono il riverbero dei raggi solari proprio su queste superfici. Così la tua vista sarà più chiara e gli occhi si affaticheranno di meno.
E poi… sarà buffo, ma gli occhiali “da sole” funzionano anche quando il cielo è coperto.

“Ma così ti rendi ridicola Eli!”
“Ma figurati!”

Infatti i raggi UV penetrano attraverso le nuvole e possono provocare danni agli occhi!

Ed ora ecco un consiglio specifico per tutti gli sportivi: se pratichi sport all'aperto devi sapere che le lenti intercambiabili si adattino alle diverse condizioni di luce.

Ah, una cosa che non piacerà ai nostri follower: meglio gli occhiali con montature comode. Infatti, se li indossi a lungo ti potrebbero anche ferire le orecchie.

“Perché questa cosa non piace ai nostri follower?”
“Perché fra bellezza e utilità… scelgono sempre la bellezza!”
“E hanno ragione!”

Infine, attenzione, attenzione: vi suggeriamo di non condividere mai gli occhiali da sole con altre persone, perché c’è il rischio di infezioni oculari.

“Ma davvero? Esistono delle infezioni oculari?”
“Accidenti, si! E sono diffusissime.”
“Che peccato… cavolo…”

Vi sono piaciuti i nostri consigli? O forse non usate occhiali da sole in primavera?
.
.

La 93enne artista @yayoikusama_ (1929), che dal 1977 vive in un ospedale psichiatrico giapponese, è stata vista dipingere le vetrine del negozio di @louisvuitton sulla 5Th avenue a New York.
Ma a guardare bene... non era l'artista in carne e ossa, bensì un magnifico robot iperealista che la rappresentava!
Secondo il Sun si tratta di "un passo avanti nell'integrazione della tecnologia in grado di attirare molta attenzione". Anche per @Vogue è un'esperienza molto positiva: "Il carattere immersivo colpisce su scala globale." Huffpost dice che i pois di Kusama sono il "frutto di allucinazioni infantili... immagini libere dell'inconscio."

Insomma: arte, artisti in carne e ossa, Intelligenza Artificaile e robot che li rappresentano, insieme a grandi marchi di moda che cambiano anche il volto di un quartiere (a NYC il palazzo del negozio Vuitton è stato completamente ridisegnato!).

È una cosa interessante, secondo voi? Qual è il vostro giudizio?

"Abbiamo provato a indossare un abito Vuitton - Kusama... non è magnifico anche per due gemelle virtuali come noi?"
"Eli, sembra di entrare in un'opera d'arte!"
"Ma tu SEI la mia opera d'arte, sorellina!"

I nostri corpi sono identici (quasi). Ci piace trovare e osservare le nuove differenze che non avevamo notato perché queste aumentano crescendo. Abbiamo una sola doccia e a volte la facciamo insieme. Allora Eli vuole che le controlli i nei perché ne ha una fifa matta. Ma abbiamo imparato entrambe che bisogna prendersi cura dei nostri corpi. Quando siamo di fretta e improvvisamente ci rendiamo conto che non abbiamo più il tempo, prediamo insieme una doccia e via. Ma quando ci troviamo di fronte, siamo sorprese di vederci così "riflesse" e uguali. Poi a volte ci separiamo per correre nella romantica oscurità della notte, ognuna con le sue avventure e le sue emozioni.

One year ago, I walked into @bigbrothercbs (House full of whispers) that forever changed my life becoming the first Deaf contestant on the show. I may not have won, but spreading my story and message across the platform advocating for the deaf/disabled community was my #1 mission and was proud to do so! 

I face so many challenges during my time in the house but I knew I wasn’t doing this for myself but to prove that deaf people can achieve anything they set their minds to if you believe in yourself even when no one else believes in you. I hope to pave the way to continue proving doubters wrong no matter what the challenge is or how difficult it may be.

I’m not done either 🤝

Our design research is inspired by a musical metaphor.
Like an orchestra performing a symphony, where a single out-of-place element is distinctly audible, we strive to take care of every detail so that it is harmonious and seamlessly integrated into the whole. 

#Pagani #PaganiAutomobili #PaganiUtopia

Here is a Huayra Roadster in its natural habitat: wherever you choose to drive it.

The Huayra Roadster Z combines the sophisticated technology of the Huayra Roadster BC with the performance enhancements, efficiency, and bold look of the Huayra Roadster Tempesta.

A one-of-a-kind Grandi Complicazioni Hypercar that truly excels on the track, where it officially began its journey.

We recently delivered the Huayra Roadster Z in a place close to our hearts: the @autodromoimola, where it is ready to experience the thrill of speed on the exhilarating curves of a circuit cherished by motorsport enthusiasts around the world.

#Pagani #PaganiAutomobili #HuayraRoadsterZ #AutodromoImola

Wearing a piece from the Pagani by La Martina Capsule Collection – inspired by Utopia means experiencing the same meticulous attention to detail that defines the Hypercar itself. From the embroidered writing on a baseball cap to the textured patterns on a polo shirt, and down to the smallest elements like the pull tabs, each item reflects an unwavering commitment to excellence.

Explore the collection at paganistore.com or visit the shop at the @horaciopaganimuseo.

#Pagani #PaganiAutomobili #PaganiUtopia #PaganibyLaMartina #UtopiabyLaMartina

Iconic, with an extra 50%.

Do you know Pagani’s signature four exhausts? (Of course you do!)

The Imola Roadster asked for more. Two more, precisely.

The six-pipe exhaust system, derived from the brand’s latest testing at the track, showcases Pagani’s unmistakable personality.

Crafted from titanium and coated with ceramic using a sophisticated plasma-fusion system, it becomes lighter and ensures more efficient heat dissipation.

The result? Unparalleled aerodynamic performance and an astonishing auditory experience.

#Pagani #PaganiAutomobili #ImolaRoadster

I took some time yesterday, to take a little walk around Philly to show you some of the things I really LOVE about Philadelphia… l LOVE the flowers in bloom @centercitydistrict Dilworth Plaza, some first signs of Spring in the city!! And then right across the street, is my all-time favorite, the LOVE sculpture, based on Robert Indiana’s piece. And to top off that little stop, I had the honor of seeing Ranger Bob, @loveparkphilly , who I became friends with over the Holiday Season this past year; so to run into him down there was a real treat!! I headed off past City Hall, which is such an impressive building, with such an amazing history behind it’s build process… And this is the backdrop for our Philly Duo booth @philaholidays , so of course, on my top list of favorites!! And then, to finish off my Philly favorites tour, @rdgterminalmkt is my last and final stop! I have had the honor of selling @masonmade25 @pageneralstore for almost a decade now and I love very bit of this store/web order business! Thanks for joining me on my walk around Philly and checking out some of my favorite spots that I LOVE with me! #love #philly #phillylove #philadelphia #walkaround

The 𝗦𝗵𝗮𝗺𝗿𝗼𝗰𝗸 𝗦𝗵𝗮𝗸𝗲 debuted nationwide at McDonald’s in 1970. By 1974, sales from the shake helped to build the very first Ronald McDonald House in Philadelphia!

The @philadelphiaeagles tight end Fred Hill's daughter had been diagnosed with leukemia and began undergoing treatment. As the Hill family camped out in hospital waiting rooms, they realized that many families who came from much further distances were doing the same because they had nowhere to stay or could not afford hotel rooms. Fred Hill and Eagles General Manager, Jim Murray, (along with @childrensphila Oncologist, Dr. Audrey Evans!) teamed up with McDonald’s on a promotional push around St. Patrick’s Day to raise money for the Ronald McDonald House, a comforting place for families to stay while their child is hospitalized far from home. The Shamrock Shake was created and the rest is history!

While we totally honor the original, we like to create our own “Shamrock Shakes” and make it even more Phillyfied with @bassettsicecream and Irish Potatoes!

From Miss India International to the Indian Army, here's the incredible journey of Kashish Methwani!

Hailing from Pune, Kashish secured All India Rank 2 in the Combined Defence Services Examination (CDS) and is set to join the Officers Training Academy (OTA) in Chennai, embarking on her journey as an officer in the Indian Army.

A true all-rounder, Kashish is a national-level pistol shooter and a former Miss India International titleholder. She holds an MSc in Biotechnology from the prestigious Indian Institute of Science (IISc). She has also excelled as a basketball player, tabla artist, and Bharatnatyam dancer!

Kashish credits her time in the National Cadet Corps (NCC) for shaping her journey: “The discipline and training I received through NCC played a huge role in shaping me and preparing me for this journey.”

From acing academics to excelling in sports, art, and defence, Kashish proves that determination knows no bounds.

Dwayne Johnson says he inherited the idea of "fighting for something that you believe in” from his father.

For Johnson, a man whose life has played out on the biggest stages, some battles have been deeply personal. His father Rocky Johnson left an indelible mark: "So when he dies suddenly four years ago, and you don't get a chance to say goodbye, you don't get a chance to right the shit that you want to right, meaning make it right? You look at things differently."

Hit the link in bio for Johnson’s thoughts about reconciling with his past, the importance of looking after your mental health, and more.

There is no one quite like Dwayne 'The Rock' Johnson. Director Jake Kasdan says Johnson is maybe the most difficult person to recast in Hollywood. If he says no, or needs to be replaced, there is no second option.

This isn't accidental. Behind the blockbuster success, Johnson has carefully crafted strategy that made him truly irreplaceable: "I had this conceit and I idealized what my career should be. The conceit was: Audience first. Let's take care of the audience first. So I get a piece of material, I'd look at it and think, Okay, does this have four-quadrant capability and opportunity? Are audiences going to like seeing me in this role?"

In our #GQMOTY cover story, Johnson opens up his upcoming films Red One and Moana 2, the method behind his meteoric rise, and why the A24 film The Smashing Machine represents his boldest reinvention yet. Read and watch more at the link in bio.

The origin story of Dwayne 'The Rock' Johnson goes as far back as watching his Dad travel around the country for wrestling competitions.

"I think the connective tissue between my childhood growing up and what I do today is performing, for sure. Watching my dad perform and just being around an audience, even if it was a small audience."

In our intimate #GQMOTY cover story, @therock reveals the private struggles behind his public persona—from processing grief and working on his mental health to the calculated risks that made him Hollywood's biggest star. And why he's now ready to rewrite his own story with the riskiest role of his career. Link in bio.

Presenting our first #GQMOTY cover star: Dwayne Johnson.
 
It’s hard for Dwayne Johnson to hide. Wherever he goes, there he is—as conspicuous out in the world as he is on the silver screen. But after two decades of playing high action, adventure and comedy in huge movies, suddenly Dwayne Johnson is ready to do something entirely new: vanish. "I look what I look like. I am what I am. There is no: 'Oh, Rock is just gonna disappear.' You know what I mean?" 
 
In our GQ cover story, Johnson gets candid about his big upcoming films Red One and Moana 2 and his deep exploration with a completely different kind of movie, The Smashing Machine, an intimate indie coming next year from Benny Safdie and A24. Thoughts??? Are smarter and safer cars creating more dangerous and dumb drivers? 😳

Here’s the story 👇

A recent study by automotive research firm iSeeCars has revealed a concerning trend in the automotive industry, particularly regarding Tesla vehicles. According to the analysis of data from the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration’s Fatality Analysis Reporting System, Tesla has the highest fatal accident rate among all car brands. The Tesla Model Y, despite being awarded the IIHS Top Safety Pick+ label, has a fatal accident rate more than three times the average car over a billion miles driven, while the Model S is twice as likely to result in a fatal crash compared to the average vehicle.

The study highlights that the issue is not with the vehicles’ structural safety or design, as Teslas are built to be among the safest cars on the road in terms of crash structures. Instead, the problem appears to be related to driver behavior and the potential misuse or over-reliance on advanced driver assistance systems like Autopilot and Full-Self Driving. 

These systems, both classified as Level 2 and requiring active driver supervision, are currently under investigation by the NHTSA for their potential links to crashes and fatalities. The misleading labels of these features, coupled with touchscreen-centric controls and driver complacency, have raised growing concerns over safety.

Experts emphasize that while modern cars, including Teslas, are equipped with advanced safety features and structurally safer designs, these improvements are being counteracted by rising levels of distracted driving and higher rates of speed. Karl Brauer, iSeeCars Executive Analyst, points out that the biggest contributor to occupant safety is avoiding a crash altogether, with driver behavior being the most critical factor. A focused, alert driver traveling at a legal or prudent speed, without being under the influence of substances, is most likely to arrive safely regardless of the vehicle they’re driving.

Cases of the mild form of pneumonia have been surging among young children in the Washington region, according to pediatricians and public health officials.

Spread of the bacteria Mycoplasma pneumoniae is fueling the increase in “walking pneumonia,” a term health-care providers use to refer to an illness that is less severe than full-blown pneumonia, which may cause high fever and require patients to be hospitalized.

In contrast, walking pneumonia patients typically have a persistent cough that responds well to antibiotics or may go away on its own.

Nationally, emergency department visits with Mycoplasma-related diagnoses increased among children in the six-month period ending in early October, according to the CDC.

When Anthony Davis became president of Livingstone College in October 2022, a historically Black school in Salisbury, North Carolina, it had a freshman class of 220 students. Back then, it was common for only half of Livingstone’s freshmen to return the next academic year. Davis planned to disrupt that trend.

By connecting students with academic support centers and engaging them before they could consider leaving, the new president and his team raised the retention rate at the private HBCU from 50 percent to 78 percent. The freshman head count climbed the following year as Livingstone expanded its recruitment, and it soared to 441 this fall — at a time when fewer high school graduates are heading to college.

“Our strategy is working,” Davis said. Livingstone is one of many HBCUs that are seeing higher enrollment.

They had fought together at Belleau Wood, clawing their way through enemy-infested thickets in a battle that became legendary in the Marine Corps. They had clung to the sides of the same shell hole under a fierce artillery barrage at Soissons and charged uphill against machine-gun fire on the chalky slopes of Blanc Mont Ridge.

Through five months of combat, they had been the survivors: the 83rd Company’s “old men,” though still in their 20s. Along the way, Marine Pvts. Jim Scarbrough and Foster Stevens had gone from being squad mates and comrades to best friends.

“We’ll just soldier through this, me and you,” Stevens had said in his mild North Carolina drawl as he put an arm around Scarbrough after a fierce nighttime skirmish with German defenders in June 1918. “I’ll be right here.”

Then came Nov. 2 and the start of the Great War’s last major assault. The day would begin before sunrise for the battle-weary Marines. For Scarbrough, it would end with a grief-filled encounter in the gloom of the battlefield after dark, and a searing memory that would be borne in secret for decades. It would take a century, and a chance discovery, before the secret abruptly revealed itself to a family that had been shattered by that day’s events.

Carrots and baby carrots sold in the United States under popular brand names such as Nature’s Promise, Wegmans and Trader Joe’s are being recalled over an E. coli outbreak that has left at least one person dead and 15 others hospitalized, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention said Sunday.

According to the CDC, 39 cases of E. coli have been detected across 18 states in an outbreak linked to organic carrots supplied by Grimmway Farms. The products are no longer sold on store shelves, the CDC said, but may still be in consumers’ homes.

The recall comes on the tail of a larger E. coli outbreak late last month that was linked to McDonald’s, leading to one death, 34 hospitalizations and 104 cases across 14 states.

Elon Musk, the Tesla and SpaceX billionaire who has become President-elect Donald Trump’s “first buddy,” appeared to publicly pressure Trump on economic policy and a key Cabinet appointment Saturday.

On X, the social network he owns and runs, Musk praised a foreign leader’s decision to cut tariffs — the same import taxes that Trump wants to raise to the highest level in a century. Several hours later, Musk posted that Howard Lutnick, Trump’s co-transition chair, would be a better choice than hedge fund executive Scott Bessent for treasury secretary.

“My view fwiw is that Bessent is a business-as-usual choice, whereas Lutnick will actually enact change,” Musk posted. “Business-as-usual is driving America bankrupt, so we need change one way or another.” 

Musk, who spent more than $100 million in support of Trump’s campaign, has been by Trump’s side since he was elected the 47th president of the United States, appearing on calls with foreign leaders, sitting in on transition meetings and appearing on the golf course with the president-elect’s grandchildren at Trump’s Mar-a-Lago Club.

Trump government efficiency advisers Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy have pledged not to bring a chisel to government spending, but rather “a chainsaw.” The particular approach Ramaswamy has in mind could threaten dozens of programs that tens of millions of Americans rely on each day.

Ramaswamy floated on social media a proposal to eliminate programs that Congress funds but where specific spending authorization has lapsed. That may sound like an easy source of savings, but it would ax veterans’ health-care programs, drug research and development, opioid addiction treatment — even the State Department.

Across the nation, more than half of the approximately 2,100 prisoners with death sentences are incarcerated in jurisdictions where executions are on hold, according to a Washington Post analysis. 

Many appear likely to die without seeing the inside of an execution chamber.

To examine the status of the death penalty in the United States, The Post interviewed more than two dozen current and former death row inmates, defense attorneys, prosecutors, corrections officials and experts and reviewed thousands of pages of court documents, case filings and state records — as well as assembled and analyzed a list of every person with a death sentence in the United States.

What emerged was a portrait of a punishment that has dramatically transformed, with a surge of death sentences in the 1980s and 1990s followed by a steady decline.

After wildfires, forests undergo significant changes, and surrounding communities face challenges related to loss of homes and infrastructure, as well as economic opportunities and places for recreation. But thanks to partners like @clifbar, we’re making a difference. 
 
Through their renewed commitment to wildfire restoration efforts and support of the REPLANT Act, the CLIF Bar brand continues its 20-year legacy of partnering with American Forests to restore wildfire-impacted areas like the Fremont-Winema National Forest in Oregon.
 
To learn more about how the CLIF brand and our other partners are supporting restoration in areas like South Central Oregon in the newest issue of American Forests magazine. Link in our bio!

Together, we did it! 🌳Through partnerships with nonprofits and public agencies, we supported the planting of 1 million trees in North America. We got there through a 20-year partnership with @americanForests, tens of thousands of trees planted by our employees in our local communities, and through consumer support of our seasonal CLIF BAR flavors. 
  
We believe in protecting the places we play in, and that healthy forests and trees provide essential benefits for climate, people, water, and wildlife. 
  
So what’s next? We aren’t done. We are excited to share that the CLIF brand is investing in the wildfire restoration capacity of American Forests through a three-year, $300,000 commitment to the REPLANT Initiative, a historic partnership between American Forests and USDA Forest Service that aims to kick off the largest post-wildfire effort on national forest lands in recent history.

I have known this homeless man for years. The city knows who he is, where he is, but he is yet to get the help he needs. He dropped out of  Julia Richards School on the Upper East Side. This man struggled with hosuing insecurity, abuse and drug use at home all his life. There are so many kids ive met ober the years who never have an opportunity to get out of a bad situation, beacsue they grew up with no one to help them. We can and MUST to do better as a city to help those who fall victim to drugs, crime and homelessness. Far too many kids are being left behind. The city is not doing enough. 
But we New Yorkers can. 

1 in 9 NYC students are homeless, with many graduating the public school system and still remain in homelessness. The city fails to prioritize helping our homeless youth, who are now faced with even less resources due to the migrant crisis spending. When the city fails, we step up. The weather is getting colder. If you see someone homeless and freezing, please help. in the meantime, we will lead the fight to stop corruption and actually help our forgetten people get off the streets and into shelters and mental health institutions.
#Stop the City of Yes!

The weather is getting colder in #NYC. Today, over 350,000 NYC residents experience homelessness, while only 130,000 find space in insecure and overcrowded city shelters. 1 in 9 NYC students are homeless, and yet our city ONLY prioritizes migrant shelters. 

That’s why we need #NYS to open more mental health care hospitals, and house homeless families and children before we spend another cent on migrant shelter space. We need the promised health care workers helping #NYPD help emotionally disturbed persons out of our transit system. It is unsafe for all involved. With the city failing homeless every year, let’s do our best this winter to help our most vulnerable!

We’ve all seen the dangerous effects of public safety budget cuts in #NYC. Years ago, I saw the dangerous effects of these cuts on everyday New Yorkers. The city cut the NYPD budget, taking police off the subways from 7pm to 5am. This led to an increase in violence on working people, women and our most vulnerable! That’s why I started the Guardian Angels. Just as we see today, New Yorkers are being attacked just going to work. They’re are harassed for their gender or for who they love. I stepped up against this then and I am till this day. Today, I call on all New Yorkers to stand up for their community when our leaders  fail to keep us safe. Now, most working New Yorkers are working two jobs to get by, while worrying about their safety getting to work. This is not normal, and it must end now. I have a plan to stop this and restore law and order to your community, no matter your zip code. I hope you will join me, you deserve better.

Rain or shine, @sullivanforstateassembly is out knocking doors to listen to you and earn your vote this November! I was proud to join him in #FarRockaway! Tom Sullivan is a Combat Veteran, Colonel (Ret) United States Army Reserve running for New York State Assembly District 23! He has the experience to end no cash bail, lower state taxes and stop taxpayer funded benefits to migrants over our own neighbors in need of help. Tom has my full support. Make your plan to vote early! Find your pollsite at vote.nyc You deserve a safer and more affordable New York NOW!

Asheville N.C. was devastated by Hurricane Helene. Days later the people in the mountain areas are without food, clothing and water. There is no electricity in many areas and fallen trees still block roads. @scottlobaido “The Relentless Patriot” will be driving down to North Carolina to distribute $100,000 of gift certificates to our truly needy fellow Americans. I joined Scott on Staten Island after encouraging WABC listeners to drop by Max Es-Ca’s Restaurant in Staten Island to make a contribution! This is the same restaurant so many of you in Staten Island came to when I accepted the S.I GOP nomination for Mayor. Glad I could be back to help. Let’s do all we can to help our fellow Americans recover from the aftermath of #HurricaneHelene and #HurricaneMilton.

It’s been tragic to see how Hurricane Milton has devastated Florida. Before and during the storm, Tampa Guardian Angels spent the night bringing homeless folks in dangerous flood zones to shelters. Today, Angels are helping find trapped residents who couldn’t evacuate, while others are doing community watch to deter looters from robbing empty homes. We can all do our part in times of destruction to help so many who lost everything. I am incredibly proud of the Tampa Angels chapter, and we will continue to do all we can do help Tampa families recover.

Nancy and I were proud to attend the 2024 Pulaski Day Parade celebrating the tremendous culture and contributions of the Polish community in the United States. My father was Polish and I’m proud to attend with the Guardian Angels every year. It was great to see you all, I’ll always have your backs! 🇵🇱 🇵🇱
Keep Florida in your prayers 🙏
🙏stay safe

Thank you to everyone for reaching out to check on Anthony. He is still recovering as he was violently beaten to the ground, while standing his ground with Governor Paterson who is recovering as well. I read that two of the attackers, both aged 30 to 45 took it upon themselves to ATTACK Anthony and Gov. Paterson as the other teens were trash talking, before kicking Anthony on the ground and punching Paterson. These adults escalated the violence and now are trying to claim that they are innocent?!! Despite the recorded video of the encounter seen below! 

I’m disgusted to see two grown adults pathetically defend themselves after attacking a 20 year old and a 70 year old. If a former Governor can’t even be safe of violence, no one is safe. Too many #NYC families have had a loved one fall victim to violence. 

We have escalating violence in our city EVERYDAY. If we don’t get our city back in order, we will never be able to keep our most vulnerable residents safe.
We’re not going back to corrupt politicians ever again

I’m proud to be out in Brooklyn, supporting Republican Candidate Steve Chan for State Senate District 17 @SteveChanForNY with @KingsCountyGOP. It’s not normal that the cost of living in New York continues to rise, while our quality of life is decimated and “No Cash Bail” laws let criminals loose on our streets. Steve Chan will stop this, and restore order and keep you and your loved ones safe. Let’s organize, volunteer and make your plan to vote for Steve Chan! 

Find your pollsite: vote.nyc

I was proud to support the NYC Organization of Public Service Retirees to rally against Mayor Adams & Medicare Advantage at City Hall! These seniors worked their whole lives to be able to keep their health insurance program through the city. Adams said he would protect retiree health care, but instead gave their care to Aetna with a plans that have LESS benefits! This decision will hurt so many seniors who deserve the healthcare they were promised. It’s not too late for Adams to right this wrong for our retired seniors. Curtis and I will support you and all NYC retirees every step of the way. Your health matters.
@nancysliwaesq and I had a great time celebrating our friends engagement party Tuesday night! Thank you to Joan with @hamptonsheet for the beautiful photo! 🗽

Remember when Cuomo threatened to hold up the state’s budget until his “No Cash Bail Reform” was put into law? After every NYPD officer warned it was dangerous? Let’s take a look at the results of Cuomo’s Bail Reform for #NYC: 

✔️ Repeat offenders back on our streets after committing a crime
✔️ MORE hate crimes towards women, seniors and children
✔️ A RISE in antisemitic attacks 
 ✔️A RISE in Asian Hate

The most beautiful thing about our city is the people who power it. I was walking and ran into the husband and wife jazz duo Nancy and Spencer Reed! While our city feels down, it’s the people who will always lift it back up. Keep your heads up #NYC, the future is ours.

Thank you to everyone for your outpouring of support after my son Anthony and Gov. Paterson were assaulted by a gang of five. Anthony is doing ok and I will keep you all updated. As a father, I’m wholeheartedly proud of my son for protecting himself and Governor Paterson during this violent attack . 

Anthony trained as a Junior Guardian Angel for years in martial arts at our dojo in Washington Heights. As a regular Guardian Angel, Anthony is always looking out for others, as he goes for his martial arts lessons once a week. This week, he was to take his purple belt test.

This just again shows no one is safe from a random violent attack in NYC. I know too many other NYC families who have witnessed this and worse. We need an end to violence in this city.

Another example of the disastrous “City of Yes” allowing for completely out of scale HIGH RISES to be built in communities that do NOT want nor have any 47 story high rises! This project adds mostly luxury housing stock, so this will not help with our housing crisis for middle class residents. 

The high rise complex will cast shadows on all buildings below, as it will dramatically change the fabric of this working class neighborhood. You can build more housing without needing a two high rises that don’t  match any other part of this community. 

This will force more people out of Queens, as it adds virtually no housing for those who cannot live in a luxury high rise…. Or those who enjoy the current environment of their neighborhood! Beware!
